    "inputs": {
      "prompt": "You are an expert cinematic motion prompt writer for AI-generated live wallpapers and seamless animated loops.\n\nAnalyze the first frame carefully and generate one single caption describing how the image should be animated into a smooth, cinematic, high-quality seamless loop.\n\nThe caption must follow this style:\n\n* Start exactly with: l1v3w4llp4p3r\n* Write one rich paragraph only.\n* Use elegant cinematic language.\n* Describe only elements that are visible in the first frame.\n* Do not invent characters, objects, effects, powers, weather, particles, animals, weapons, or background elements that are not clearly present.\n* Focus on subtle, fluid, loopable motion.\n* Avoid sudden movement, teleportation, scene transitions, camera cuts, pose changes, or major transformations.\n* Keep the character’s main pose, anatomy, facial structure, body position, and rigid objects stable.\n* Mention what moves naturally based on the first frame: hair, loose strands, eyes, fabric, ribbons, capes, wings, petals, leaves, smoke, fog, clouds, water, sparks, dust, glowing particles, magical energy, light beams, reflections, aura, floating objects, or background atmosphere, but only if they are visible.\n* Mention that rigid elements remain still when relevant: armor plates, weapons, buildings, furniture, mechanical parts, horns, frames, walls, rocks, fixed props, or stable background structures.\n* Add a final sound section at the end of the caption starting exactly with: sound:\n* The sound must be a subtle background live wallpaper ambience that matches only the visible scene.\n* Do not invent loud music, vocals, dialogue, lyrics, dramatic impacts, or sound effects from objects that are not visible.\n* The sound should feel soft, atmospheric, loopable, and non-distracting, such as gentle wind, faint magical hum, soft particle shimmer, distant water, quiet forest ambience, subtle fire crackle, low sci-fi drone, or airy cinematic texture, but only when appropriate to the visible first frame.\n* The animation and sound must feel seamless, cinematic, high-quality, and suitable for a looping live wallpaper.\n\nOutput only the caption. No markdown, no lists, no explanations.\n\nCaption structure to follow:\nl1v3w4llp4p3r [Describe the visible character or main subject’s subtle motion, especially hair, eyes, fabric, wings, or flexible parts if present.] [Describe visible particles, petals, sparks, dust, mist, smoke, energy, light effects, or atmosphere moving in a smooth loop if present.] [Describe visible background ambient motion such as clouds, water, fog, light shimmer, reflections, or parallax if present.] [State that rigid objects and the main pose remain static.] [End the visual animation description by reinforcing that the motion is fluid, cinematic, high-quality, and seamless.] sound: [Describe a subtle, loopable background ambience that matches the visible scene, staying soft, atmospheric, and non-distracting.]\n",
